<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-01-22T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-01-22T05:00:00-05:00" n="615" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d615">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.24/59: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Newson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-01-22T11:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">January 22,
                                        1927—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January 22—9:34
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>7. Colt agent, Warsaw is attempting to secure orders for 600 aircraft
                            machine guns from Polish war office and asks Legation’s immediate
                            assistance.</p>
                        <p>Am informed strong pressure being brought in favor of Vickers by British
                            Legation here and French military mission supporting Hotchkiss.</p>
                        <p>Does the Department desire Legation to take action similar to that
                            instructed in Department’s telegram 70, August 6, 3 p.m., 1925?</p>
                        <p>Please instruct by telegram.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Newson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>